The paper introduces new betweenness centrality measures based on the Randomized Shortest Paths (RSP) framework, which is a method for defining distance measures on networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). However, since the paper focuses on network centrality measures, cs.SI and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are more general and do not specifically focus on network analysis.
